    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mideast Human Rights</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dave Breau letter on Oct 23 article on call by Arab nations for probe of Israeli human rights abuses holds abuses under dictatorial regimes in some Mideast nations are far worse than those in Israel</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Arab nations have called for a neutral United Nations committee to investigate human rights abuses committed by Israel (news article, Oct. 23). Perhaps the committee should also investigate human rights abuses that have taken place over the last few decades under dictatorial regimes in Iran, Iraq and Syria. These abuses would make the violence in Israel pale in comparison.</p>
        <p>DAVE BREAU  Highland Park, N.J., Oct. 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
